<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00Sonora/491: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Nogales</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Damm</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nogales, Ariz</hi></placeName>., <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-02T23:00:00-06:00">April 2, 1929—11
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 3—1:41 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Department’s April 2, 6 p.m. This Consulate has no information at present
                            time regarding wounding of Terry [<hi rend="italic">Harry</hi>] Baker at
                            Naco, Arizona, further than that contained in press dispatch which
                            probably gave accurate account.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Damm</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>